  "text": "As a result of numerous studies describing roles for metabolites of AA in the regulation of vascular tone, there has been considerable interest in the possible involvement of these fatty acid derivatives in the signaling pathways underlying arteriolar myogenic reactivity. Evidence has been provided for their direct participation in the signaling process [CITATION_1] and as secondary modulators (144) of myogenic tone. The possible involvement of such metabolites is strengthened by the suggestion that activation of phospholipase enzymes (see sect. IVC5) during a myogenic response would liberate the required AA from membrane phospholipids. An outline of the metabolic pathways involving AA is shown in Figure 9 .",
